==English==

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/əˈpɒl.ə.dʒɪ/}}
* {{audio|en-us-apology.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Etymology===
''Defense, justification'', from [[w:Vulgar Latin|Late Latin]] '''[[apologia]]''', from [[w:Ancient Greek|Greek]] '''[[ἀπολογία]]''' ''a speech in defense'', from '''[[ἀπολογοῦμαι]]''' ''I speak in one's defense'', from '''[[ἀπόλογος]]''' ''an account, story'', from '''[[ἀπό]]''' ''from, off'' (see ''[[apo-]]'') + '''[[λόγος]]''' ''speech''.

===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
{{en-noun|apologies}}

# What you say when you [[regret]] saying or doing something [[affect]]ing others.
# A formal [[justification]], [[defence]].

